  "name": "Morrison COU2 — MRL 5 fully-assessed credibility package (NC-3 negative control)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for regulatory submission of a Class III CPB device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed at high rigor (requiredLevel 4 or 5, achievedLevel meeting or exceeding requirement). Full UQ and global sensitivity analysis are linked. This package is a clean negative-control reference: no weakener should fire.",
